##The main course is reserved for Jianjian's son-in-law of the mountain of Fire God: The diary of the old people in Wuhan fighting the plague

MICRO-SIGNAL RENDAXINWENXI

Function Introduction, Journalism Department of School of Journalism, Renmin University of China runs the platform of news gathering, editing, evaluation and photography teaching and practice.

[ editor's note ]
On the 28th, we received a letter from a reader named "Chen Xiang, " a retired Wuhan native who is staying with her husband, daughter and son-in-law in Kong Hon, Wuhan: As of 2400 hours on January 29,2020, a total of 2,261 cases of COVID-19 pneumonia and 129 deaths have been reported in Wuhan. The city of Wuhan is being written about in all sorts of ways. All kinds of emotions are amplified, all kinds of "big words" frequently reported.

Disaster Ruthless, but life still to go on, "Chen Xiang" with very simple words, recorded her as a person in the rear, while struggling to maintain the normal operation of the small family, a look at the city's special conditions: the daughter's "armed" before going to the supermarket, the son-in-law's muddy legs after returning from the construction site, the long-lost Sunny Day, the rare pig's foot soup... life is flowing, the record itself is a form of resistance.

Today is the second day of the New Year. I haven't left home for four days.

I spent most of the day in the living room, doing needlework that I always wanted to do but didn't have time to do, and my husband and kids kept swiping their phones.

Occasionally stand in the air platform to look around, quiet, like no one general. Occasionally one or two pedestrians, wearing masks, hurried past, usually crowded roads lying quietly noiseless.

Armed to the teeth, the girl entered the supermarket with fewer goods than usual, and the few customers silently selected the necessities of life, without the usual hubbub.

January 5, we should also be uncle phase invited home to meet, no one mentioned pneumonia. The city to distribute garden tickets, held 10,000 banquets normal, as always.

The girl had planned to go to Guangzhou on the 26th to play, privately heard that the epidemic is serious, on the 19th to return the ticket, and immediately notify her in-laws pick up darling to leave Wuhan. I said she was making a mountain out of a molehill, but I didn't think it was that big a deal. Not Really.

I was also planning to take advantage of them to take the baby away, I also go out for a walk, self-drive to Guangxi a walk. From then on, girls wore masks when they went out, and I had to put mine on. I also experienced SARS, feeling not as terrible as she said, before the closure of the city did not wear a mask to go out. Because I'm taking my grandson. I don't get out much.

I remember it was a sunny day and I was busy at home washing and drying. The in laws arrived in the evening, and the next morning they rushed out of Wuhan with Darling. I stayed in Wuhan with my husband, daughter and son-in-law.

Husband did not retire, he is working on the site, every holiday site to arrange personnel on duty, he was on duty on the fifth and sixth day. The girl unit also has to be on duty, her New Year's Day on duty. The son-in-law works on the construction site. He can't leave. The Girl son-in-law must wait until the unit after these New Year arrangements to leave. So they booked tickets for the second day of the Lunar New Year. But then, even if you wanted to go out, you couldn't go out in eighth grade.

Watching TV on the evening of the 20th, Academician Zhong Nanshan confirmed that pneumonia in Wuhan can be passed from person to person. I don't usually believe in gossip. From what I've seen on TV, it should be accurate. But most people still feel far away from themselves. Because no one says who has it around them. That night, the government, enterprises of all kinds of party, annual meeting, group visits, cultural performances continued as usual, people celebrate the New Year, what to do.

It began to rain on the 21st.

On the 22nd, I went to the supermarket to buy supplies for the New Year. The supermarket is very lively, people come and go, people make noise, a holiday atmosphere. People are still jubilant, few people wear masks, most people do not feel the epidemic is like a mountain pressure. I think the family is not much, also did not buy how much supplies, enough to eat a few days on the line.

23, a natural wake up, picked up a mobile phone to see: notice the city's Public Transport Stop! You have to wear a mask when you go out! Such a big city, you want to close it? This has got to be serious. At this time on television also reported more, people's concern turned to the epidemic, concern about how many new daily, online related content has gradually increased.

Aware of the severity of the outbreak, she went out wearing a mask and stopped visiting relatives and friends. She only called. Even siblings only call. If you don't go out, you can do something you normally want to do but don't have time to do.

My mother and sister live together, in the opposite community, across a small road, did not go to visit. Old Mother is also aware of high, do not call the initiative to come. We don't panic when people around us don't get it. Just stay home, don't go out. It had never been so quiet.

A cousin of my family, the family went out to play years ago, the plan is to rush back, did not expect the passage into and out of Wuhan have been suspended, only in the new year. Full refund from the airline. Big Cousin's family. The only way they'd let them in was if they stayed in a room, scared the hell out of them, explained everything.

Also that day, the son-in-law was informed that he had to go to Caidian District early tomorrow morning to participate in the construction of the Wuhan version of "Xiaotangshan" .

On the morning of the 324th, my son-in-law got up and went to Caidian District. It was just me, my husband and my daughter at home. And the streets are quiet.

In the evening, until the end of the Spring Festival gala, son-in-law did not return home, shoes are full of mud, exhausted. I took off my coat and quickly served him hot food. My son-in-law told me about the 24-hour construction of the construction site while eating. Then we slept until the New Year's Day.

New Year's Eve, the son-in-law and went to the construction site to replace the day shift staff. It was not until the middle of the second day of the New Year that the son-in-law, who had been working all night, came home covered in mud.

From zero hour on the 26th, Wuhan Motor vehicle restrictions, feel the beginning is closed city, can not control, then on the three towns cut off, let you not in the city all over. Son-in-law gave the license plate number, drove his car to Caidian District every day. We're in the Kong Hon district, forty kilometers from Caidian District, Empty City, no traffic, half an hour.

On the 27th, I woke up to a message on my mobile phone. A person I knew was diagnosed with new type pneumonia last night. Immediately ask about his close friends who have had contact with him. Fortunately, the people with whom he is currently in contact are all well and isolated from each other at home. I hope everything is all right!

In order to solve the hospital to see more patients, if there is fever first to the community clinic. But the community clinic's protection is worse than the hospital's. More people, fewer ambulances, fewer beds. As long as it's nothing serious, write yourself a prescription and stay home. Now she can't even have a normal disease.

Early in the morning, the son-in-law also set off for the construction site in Caidian District, I do not know what time to return. Every time he came home from the day shift at 11 o'clock in the evening, he did not return until 10 o'clock in the morning. I was tired when I came back. It had been rainy days and mud on my feet. We asked him to pay attention, but he said so many people, how to pay attention? It's impossible. It's impossible.

It's been five days since I left home today, and my vegetables are getting smaller and smaller. Only three major local supermarkets are still in operation, to protect people's daily life supplies, home supplies can withstand a few days, adhere to! Protective supplies are guaranteed for the son-in-law, we do not go out, the demand is not big. In the morning, eat chicken soup, eat dumplings; in the afternoon, eat chicken soup, eat dumplings, bread.

My daughter and I at home, only two meals a day, when the right to lose weight, the main course to the son-in-law is still in the struggle to eat. Three meals to two meals, one is to sleep naturally wake up later, again is no activity, nor hungry, there is also want to extend the use of materials, eat a few days.

The pneumonia epidemic in Wuhan has spread to all areas except Tibet in China. TV and the Internet broadcast the latest developments of the epidemic every day, with new outbreaks every day.

In the home can hear the sound of small community fire truck circuit broadcast, admonish residents do not go out, try to stay at home, go out must wear a mask.

Today is the fourth day of the New Year, six days did not go out, quiet outside. Occasionally on the road there are one or two private cars passing, one or two pedestrians wearing masks into the opposite of the Zhongbai Small Supermarket. A health insurance sentinel clinic across the street is still open. Patients with fever should first contact the community medical clinic to relieve the burden on the hospital.

Last night, the owners of the Community Wechat Group are retweeting: 8 o'clock to open the window, sing together "national anthem" , "I and my motherland. ". At exactly eight o'clock in the evening, I stood on the air-rack and hooted "go, Wuhan! " Because it was too empty and not very focused. These days, the residents suffocate... At last some voices were heard. I heard a faint voice singing, can not say what feeling, the eyes suddenly moist.

This morning, a ray of sunlight came through the crack in the window. I took advantage of the sun, cleaning quilt cover, clothing.

Son-in-law at home for dinner, the husband made four dishes, a family swept away. Usually son-in-law is not at home to eat, the three of us are eating dumplings or noodles, porridge, on the salted fish, Bacon.

Girl, son-in-law go to the supermarket to buy some vegetables, the supermarket than the previous two days more obvious, with leafy vegetable shelves have been robbed of instant noodles, only meat is also sufficient. They ended up buying snacks and the last packet of instant noodles. Sitting on the SOFA, comfortably eating snacks, only feel that the bones and joints seem to have rust.

Stewed pig's foot soup for dinner, pancakes. Tomorrow, son-in-law will go to the construction site, I heard that the foundation construction of Vulcan Mountain Hospital is near the end. Son-in-law said that this time some of the private sector is really good. Because Machinery, materials are not enough, to find private deployment, some private price at cost. Some drivers are more tired than others. People can rest, but the machinery does not rest, the driver is limited, their working hours are also long.

There are those who are responsible.

I wish I'd heard "no new infections" tomorrow.

This article is based on the contribution of dust and interviews to do some additional collation


Small Editor: Excuse me, are you from Wuhan? How long have you lived in Wuhan?
Chen Xiang: I am from Wuhan. I went out to work for 10 years. Then I came back to Wuhan and worked until I retired.

Xiao Bian: Do you think the city closure and traffic restrictions in Wuhan have had any impact on your life?
Dust Incense: for me, just can not go out, shut at home. I finally get a break, and it's in this three-by-four room.
Without a patient in the house, it feels bearable. Just don't go out. Stay home and watch TV and movies.
The morning also said that the closure of the city for US good, noon to dump a garbage door can not open. Call the store. They're all back home. Fortunately, her husband at home, sitting with a stool to play for a long time, finally can open the door, but can only open from the inside, the outside can not open. We're GONNA have to keep people in the house. Make it to the store. Fengcheng, the home is not affected by the situation, there is a little situation on the inconvenience.

Editor: How do you think the mentality of the people around you changes with the emphasis on the epidemic?
Chenxiang: When the city was sealed off, people were scared and frightened, and as time went on, people accepted the isolation. Right now, it's just people who have to be outside because of work, people who might come into contact with it, people who might get infected. We are also growing awareness of the epidemic, go out consciously wear a mask, try not to touch things outside.
Then there is already six or seven days of self-isolation, no symptoms, the heart is also relieved.

Xiao Bian: Your son-in-law built Wuhan version of "Xiaotangshan" (Huoshenshan hospital) after the family life and what changes? Are there any other family members involved in the fight against the disease?
Dust Incense: worry about him AH, in contact with more people, afraid of his infection AH. Let him wash his hands, take off his coat, take a bath and give him vitamin C water to drink. He eats at home, we eat dinner, he doesn't eat at home, we just eat. Save the limited dinner for him.
My brother-in-law civil servant, Chinese New Year has not been a break. My cousin is the same, to the village door to door propaganda, tell the villagers.

Xiao Bian: in addition to medical staff, there are many people in Wuhan also struggle in the first line.
Dust: Yes. The community, the property, the cleaning, the local supermarket, they're all on the job. The medical staff is the life-saving, these personnel are the support service, so many people's city also must live.

Editor: Do you support your family to fight against the epidemic? Do you feel anything other than worry?
Dust Incense: people say the country is in trouble, every man is responsible. The city's in trouble, and it's to blame. In addition to worrying about their loved ones, they also feel the dedication of ordinary people. Online do not believe, but the actual people around the matter is believe. The girls had people they knew, so they organized their own deliveries to the hospital.

A health insurance sentinel clinic across the street is still open. Patients with fever should first contact the community medical clinic to relieve the burden on the hospital.

Last night, the owners of the Community Wechat Group are retweeting: 8 o'clock to open the window, sing together "national anthem" , "I and my motherland. ". At exactly eight o'clock in the evening, I stood on the air-rack and hooted "go, Wuhan! " Because it was too empty and not very focused. These days, the residents suffocate... At last some voices were heard. I heard a faint voice singing, can not say what feeling, the eyes suddenly moist.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This morning, a ray of sunlight came through the crack in the window. I took advantage of the sun, cleaning quilt cover, clothing.

Son-in-law at home for dinner, the husband made four dishes, a family swept away. Usually son-in-law is not at home to eat, the three of us are eating dumplings or noodles, porridge, on the salted fish, Bacon.

Girl, son-in-law go to the supermarket to buy some vegetables, the supermarket than the previous two days more obvious, with leafy vegetable shelves have been robbed of instant noodles, only meat is also sufficient. They ended up buying snacks and the last packet of instant noodles. Sitting on the SOFA, comfortably eating snacks, only feel that the bones and joints seem to have rust.

Stewed pig's foot soup for dinner, pancakes. Tomorrow, son-in-law will go to the construction site, I heard that the foundation construction of Vulcan Mountain Hospital is near the end. Son-in-law said that this time some of the private sector is really good. Because Machinery, materials are not enough, to find private deployment, some private price at cost. Some drivers are more tired than others. People can rest, but the machinery does not rest, the driver is limited, their working hours are also long.

There are those who are responsible.

I wish I'd heard "no new infections" tomorrow.

Small Editor: Excuse me, are you from Wuhan? How long have you lived in Wuhan?
Chen Xiang: I am from Wuhan. I went out to work for 10 years. Then I came back to Wuhan and worked until I retired.

Xiao Bian: Do you think the city closure and traffic restrictions in Wuhan have had any impact on your life?
Dust Incense: for me, just can not go out, shut at home. I finally get a break, and it's in this three-by-four room.
Without a patient in the house, it feels bearable. Just don't go out. Stay home and watch TV and movies.
The morning also said that the closure of the city for US good, noon to dump a garbage door can not open. Call the store. They're all back home. Fortunately, her husband at home, sitting with a stool to play for a long time, finally can open the door, but can only open from the inside, the outside can not open. We're GONNA have to keep people in the house. Make it to the store. Fengcheng, the home is not affected by the situation, there is a little situation on the inconvenience.

Editor: How do you think the mentality of the people around you changes with the emphasis on the epidemic?
Chenxiang: When the city was sealed off, people were scared and frightened, and as time went on, people accepted the isolation. Right now, it's just people who have to be outside because of work, people who might come into contact with it, people who might get infected. We are also growing awareness of the epidemic, go out consciously wear a mask, try not to touch things outside.
Then there is already six or seven days of self-isolation, no symptoms, the heart is also relieved.

Xiao Bian: Your son-in-law built Wuhan version of "Xiaotangshan" (Huoshenshan hospital) after the family life and what changes? Are there any other family members involved in the fight against the disease?
Dust Incense: worry about him AH, in contact with more people, afraid of his infection AH. Let him wash his hands, take off his coat, take a bath and give him vitamin C water to drink. He eats at home, we eat dinner, he doesn't eat at home, we just eat. Save the limited dinner for him.
My brother-in-law civil servant, Chinese New Year has not been a break. My cousin is the same, to the village door to door propaganda, tell the villagers.

Xiao Bian: in addition to medical staff, there are many people in Wuhan also struggle in the first line.
Dust: Yes. The community, the property, the cleaning, the local supermarket, they're all on the job. The medical staff is the life-saving, these personnel are the support service, so many people's city also must live.

Editor: Do you support your family to fight against the epidemic? Do you feel anything other than worry?
Dust Incense: people say the country is in trouble, every man is responsible. The city's in trouble, and it's to blame. In addition to worrying about their loved ones, they also feel the dedication of ordinary people. Online do not believe, but the actual people around the matter is believe. The girls had people they knew, so they organized their own deliveries to the hospital.
